  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-04-19",
    "date": "2023-11-29T18:52:27Z",
    "text": "Manufacturing API, Drugs, and Excipients in America Act or the MADE in America Act\n\nThis bill establishes a tax credit for certain manufacturers of pharmaceuticals or medical products.\n\nSpecifically, the bill establishes a tax credit for manufacturers of pharmaceuticals, active pharmaceutical ingredients, excipients (i.e., inactive ingredients), medical diagnostic devices, or personal protective equipment, if they are located in a designated distressed zone. The tax credit is equal to 25% of the manufacturer's production expenditures; the credit increases to 30% of expenditures if a substantial portion of the manufacturer's employees reside in a distressed zone.\n\nThe bill defines distressed zone as an area that has been designated as a qualified opportunity zone by the Internal Revenue Service (i.e., an economically distressed community in which certain new investments may be eligible for preferential tax treatment) and that has a poverty rate of over 30%."
  },
